aged jane who fervent protestant     september first parliament mary s reign revoked provisions edward s favoured jane s succession declaring mary brother s rightful heir denounced revoked jane s proclamation as usurper   centuries attempt alter succession mostly seen as one man plot northumberland   since  s however many historians attributed inception devise insistence its implementation king s initiative   diarmaid macculloch made out edward s teenage dreams founding evangelical realm christ   while david starkey stated edward couple co operators driving his   among other members privy council northumberland s intimate john gates suspected suggesting edward change his devise so jane herself not just any sons hers inherit crown   whatever degree his contribution edward convinced his word law   fully endorsed disinheriting his half sisters barring mary from succession cause which young king believed   referred court as jane dudley wife guildford jane charged high treason as husband two his brothers archbishop canterbury thomas cranmer   their trial special commission took place   november   guildhall city london commission chaired thomas white lord mayor london thomas howard  rd duke norfolk other members included edward stanley  rd earl derby john bourchier  nd earl bath as expected all defendants found guilty sentenced death duke suffolk also accused high treason sentenced death thanks his wife s close friendship mary temporarily saved from executed although remained under house arrest     jane s guilt having treacherously assumed title power monarch evidenced number documents signed as jane quene   sentence burned alive tower hill beheaded as queen pleases burning traditional english punishment treason committed women     imperial ambassador reported charles v holy roman emperor life spared   jane submitted letter explanation queen asking forgiveness sin accused informing majesty truth events   account spoke herself as wife who loves husband   december jane allo