fountain youth mythical spring which supposedly restores youth anyone who drinks bathes its waters tales such fountain recounted around world thousands years appearing writings herodotus  th century bc alexander romance  rd century ad stories prester john early crusades  th  th centuries ad stories similar waters also featured prominently among people caribbean during age exploration early  th century spoke restorative powers water mythical land bimini based these many legends explorers adventurers looked elusive fountain youth some other remedy aging generally associated magic waters these waters river spring any other water source said reverse aging process cure sickness when swallowed bathed legend became particularly prominent  th century when became associated spanish explorer juan ponce de le n first governor puerto rico ponce de le n supposedly searching fountain youth when traveled florida   legend native americans told ponce de le n fountain youth bimini objects sustain restore youth common ancient literature s n l qi unninni s epic gilgamesh   bce   bce describes magical plant called old man made young grows watery abyss   herodotus mentions fountain containing special kind water land macrobians which gives macrobians their exceptional longevity ichthyophagid then their turn questioned king concerning term life diet his people told most lived hundred twenty years old while some even went beyond age ate boiled flesh their drink nothing milk when ichthyophagi showed wonder number years led fountain wherein when washed found their flesh all glossy sleek as if bathed oil scent came from spring like violets water so weak said nothing float neither wood nor any lighter substance all went bottom if account fountain true their constant use water from which makes so long lived   story water life appears eastern versions alexander romance which describes alexander great his servant crossing land darkness find restorative spring servant story turn derived from middle