ert rapid eye movement hypothesis proposes hidden elements rem sleep emerge during wakefulness sleep transition stage   support comes from b dicz et al who notes greater similarity between wst wakefulness sleep transition eeg rem sleep eeg than between former stage   sleep   respiratory pattern changes also noted hypnagogic state addition lowered rate frontalis muscle activity   microsleep short episodes immediate sleep onset intrude into wakefulness any time wakefulness sleep cycle due sleep deprivation other conditions   resulting impaired cognition even amnesia   his book zen brain james h austin cites speculation regular meditation develops specialized skill freezing hypnagogic process later later stages onset sleep initially alpha wave stage later theta   early references hypnagogia found writings aristotle iamblichus cardano simon forman swedenborg   romanticism brought renewed interest subjective experience edges sleep   more recent centuries many authors referred state edgar allan poe example wrote fancies experienced only when brink sleep consciousness so   charles dickens s oliver twist there pair episodes one portrays title character experiencing hypnopompic state which precedes following episode which describes hypnagogic state there kind sleep steals upon sometimes which while holds body prisoner not free mind from sense things enable ramble its pleasure undoubted fact although our senses touch sight time dead yet our sleeping thoughts visionary scenes pass before influenced materially influenced mere silent presence some external object which not near when closed our eyes whose vicinity no waking consciousness     serious scientific inquiry began  th century johannes peter m ller jules baillarger alfred maury continued into  th century leroy   francis galton his visions sane persons   wrote maria mikha lovna manaseina wrote these phenomena attract attention certain power observation required why chiefly found intelligent persons manaseina also noted ch