ay other palaces known from historical sources from modern excavations     alhambra s western tip alcazaba fortress multiple smaller towers fortified gates also located along alhambra s walls outside alhambra walls located nearby east generalife former nasrid country estate summer palace accompanied historic orchards modern landscaped gardens     architecture nasrid palaces reflects tradition moorish architecture developed over previous centuries     characterized use courtyard as central space basic unit around which other halls rooms organized   courtyards typically water features their centre such as reflective pool fountain decoration focused inside building executed primarily tile mosaics lower walls carved stucco upper walls geometric patterns vegetal motifs arabic inscriptions main types decorative motifs additionally stalactite like sculpting known as muqarnas used three dimensional features like vaulted ceilings     alhambra derives from arabic al amr pronounced al ra meaning lit red one f complete form which al qal al amr red fortress qalat     al alhambra means arabic ignored general usage both english spanish where name normally given definite article reference colour red name due reddish colour its walls which constructed rammed earth   reddish colour comes from iron oxide local clay used type construction   most names used today specific structures locations within alhambra imaginative names coined after mediaeval period often  th century     original arabic names nasrid era buildings not known although some scholars proposed connections between certain buildings some names mentioned historical sources   evidence roman presence unclear archaeologists found remains ancient foundations sabika hill   fortress citadel probably dating from visigothic period existed hill  th century   first reference qal al amra during battles between arabs muladies during rule abdallah ibn muhammad r     according surviving documents from era red castle quite small its wall