ille   meanwhile ibn al ahmar muhammad established what became last longest reigning muslim dynasty iberian peninsula nasrids who ruled emirate granada   ibn al ahmar relatively new political player region likely came from modest background able win support consent multiple muslim settlements under threat from castilian advance   upon settling granada   ibn al ahmar initially resided old citadel zirids albaicin hill same year began construction alhambra as new residence citadel     according arabic manuscript since published as nimo de madrid y copenhague   year   abdallah ibn al ahmar climbed place called alhambra examined marked foundations castle left someone charge directing work before year passed construction ramparts completed water brought from river channel carrying water built during reign nasrid dynasty alhambra transformed into palatine city complete irrigation system composed aqueducts water channels provided water complex other nearby countryside palaces such as generalife     previously old fortresses hill dependent rainwater collected from cistern near alcazaba what brought up from darro river below     creation sultan s canal arabic romanized saqiyat al sultan which brought water from mountains east solidified identity alhambra as palace city rather than defensive ascetic structure first hydraulic system expanded afterwards included two long water channels several sophisticated elevation devices bring water onto plateau   only elements preserved from time ibn al ahmar some fortification walls particularly alcazaba western end complex     ibn al ahmar not time complete any major new palaces initially lived one towers alcazaba before later moving modest house site current palace charles v   later nasrid rulers after ibn al ahmar continuously modified site along fragile materials themselves which needed regular repairs makes exact chronology its development difficult determine     oldest major palace which some remains preserved structure known as pala